        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 2:10AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 210 AM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 7 miles east of
Stanton, or 22 miles south of Garrison, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Washburn, Underwood, Turtle Lake, Stanton, Riverdale, Pick City,
Coleharbor, Cross Ranch State Park, Falkirk, Hensler, Fort Clark, and
Lake Sakakawea State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Persons in campgrounds should seek shelter until this storm passes.</instruction>
